the eiffel parallel execution environment version fran รง aise epee ( eiffel parallel execution environment ) is an object oriented design framework for programming distributed memory parallel computers , developed within the pampa project . it proposes a programming environment where data and control parallelism are totally encapsulated in regular eiffel classes , without any extension to the language nor modification of its semantics. epee has been used to build paladin , a parallel object oriented linear algebra library . epee basic principles paladin pom library object-oriented software engineering with eiffel publications epee team why eiffel ? jezequel @ irisa.fr ( march 28 , 1995 )
